        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 6:16PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southeast of Palisade, or 19 miles southeast of Grand Junction,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Delta, Orchard City, Cedaredge, Skyway, Cory, Eckert, Austin, and
Grand Mesa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
